    "(2) The valley remains the same across the DW, such that region R is polarized in valley K and has Chern number C = -1.",
    "We dub this the Chern wall.",
    "Since the Chern numbers C L = -C R are opposite, the gapless chiral edge modes of the two domains are co-propagating.",
    "If this occurs in a patchwork fashion across a mesoscopic sample, this is referred to as a Chern mosaic [248].Neglecting the DW energy, these two solutions would be energetically degenerate.",
    "However, as well will see, the delicate energetics at the DW can tilt the system towards either solution, depending on the continuum model parameters and the gradient of the sublattice potential (set by w)."
